Here's a NGINX configuration that worked for me (@ArchangeGabriel's didn't for some reason): 

    server {
        listen 443 ssl;
        # relevant https configuration
        location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {
            return 301 http://$server_name$request_uri;
        }
    }
    server {
        listen 80;
        # relevant http configuration
        location / {
            return 301 https://$server_name$request_uri;
        }
        location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {}
    }

Not obvious: the order of the sever directives is important.

