It basically comes down to using "HTTP/1.1 Chunked Transfer Coding" on early/future segments, meaning that requests are being made ahead of time, waiting for the segments to become available and downloading them as soon as possible. The client doesn't have to wait for a segment to be finished and can consume the data immediately (pass it to the player/demuxer).
